50:05.705 --> 50:07.375
OK.

50:07.445 --> 50:09.375
Down this way.

50:11.545 --> 50:13.715
This way.

50:40.545 --> 50:42.485
A lion cub.

50:43.315 --> 50:45.545
We must tell Kazar.

50:47.285 --> 50:49.775
- It's my turn to tell him.
- You got to last time.

50:49.855 --> 50:51.555
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did!

50:55.695 --> 50:59.725
Thank you very much,
but I'm afraid I've got to run.

50:59.805 --> 51:01.235
Koalas are very busy bees.

51:01.305 --> 51:03.775
If I could...
I'll just buzz along to the door...

51:03.835 --> 51:06.035
For centuries,
we've watched our brethren

51:06.105 --> 51:08.545
perish at the claw of the lion.

51:08.615 --> 51:12.305
Today, we put our hooves down.

51:12.385 --> 51:17.345
No longer will we dwell
at the bottom of the food chain.

51:17.425 --> 51:20.755
Well, yes. I should say so.

51:20.825 --> 51:25.195
There were those who doubted
that you'd arrive to lead us.

51:25.665 --> 51:28.325
But I always believed in the Omen.

51:28.395 --> 51:32.065
The Omen! Right. Remind me again?

51:32.135 --> 51:34.405
Sent down by the gods years ago...

51:36.405 --> 51:39.395
Oh, no! Not you!

51:55.125 --> 51:57.425
<i>I'm so cuddly! I like you!</i>

52:03.475 --> 52:04.765
Oh, Great Him,

52:04.835 --> 52:08.965
you must lead us
in our transformation from prey...

52:10.645 --> 52:12.335
...to predator.

52:12.775 --> 52:16.445
Hold it. I am the Great Him?

52:18.215 --> 52:21.085
- The Great Him?
- Him.

52:22.455 --> 52:26.955
So this is all your fault!
That's it! You...!

52:27.025 --> 52:29.055
- Kazar!
- Kazar! Don't listen to him!

52:29.135 --> 52:31.565
- Kazar! Over here!
- Kazar! Over here!

52:31.635 --> 52:34.795
How dare you interrupt my audience
with the Great Him!

52:34.875 --> 52:38.235
But... but we found a lion cub!

52:39.645 --> 52:41.575
- You did?
- Was he with a big lion?

52:41.645 --> 52:44.115
With big hair? Well, a mullet, really.

52:44.185 --> 52:47.675
Oh, Great Him,
you brought two lions with you?

52:47.755 --> 52:50.015
Well, like any Great Him,

52:50.085 --> 52:52.525
I travel with an entourage.

52:53.255 --> 52:57.025
Worry not, Your Himness,
I shall have Blag bring the lions here.

52:57.095 --> 53:01.655
And he better not screw this up,
like you screwed up my dance number!

53:01.735 --> 53:03.855
I lost count for one verse.

53:03.935 --> 53:06.305
Step-kick, pivot-kick,
walk, walk, walk.

53:07.235 --> 53:10.935
Why do we even bother rehearsing?

53:12.115 --> 53:14.635
A good chorus line
is so hard to put together.

53:17.385 --> 53:18.785
Take to the skies!

53:18.855 --> 53:20.785
We're taking! We're taking!

53:22.925 --> 53:25.515
- Find them!
- Yes, sir.

53:25.595 --> 53:28.325
Bring us those lions!

53:31.795 --> 53:36.165
The gods celebrate
the fulfillment of the prophecy.

53:36.235 --> 53:38.835
We stamp our hooves

53:38.905 --> 53:41.735
in praise of the Great Him!

53:41.805 --> 53:43.635
Holy moly!

53:43.715 --> 53:45.905
<i>Holy moly
Holy moly</i>

53:45.975 --> 53:49.175
You are our king!

54:05.105 --> 54:08.395
Looky, looky who's there.

54:09.475 --> 54:10.735
Surprise!

54:13.345 --> 54:14.705
No!

54:16.745 --> 54:18.715
Sorry we're late for dinner!

54:27.725 --> 54:29.125
That's pathetic!

54:31.595 --> 54:32.755
Get off!

54:32.835 --> 54:34.795
- That didn't hurt!
- Stop!

54:38.105 --> 54:40.295
- Ryan!
- No!

54:41.645 --> 54:43.365
I'm coming, son!

54:45.015 --> 54:46.705
Dad?

54:46.775 --> 54:48.645
- Help!
- Let's scram!

54:48.715 --> 54:50.615
- Ryan!
- What are you doing here?

54:50.685 --> 54:53.315
- I can't believe it! I found you.
- How'd you find me?

54:53.385 --> 54:55.415
Are you all right? Are you hurt?

54:55.485 --> 54:57.425
- Your paw.
- I got trapped in that box.

54:57.495 --> 54:58.825
It's OK, son.

54:58.895 --> 55:01.515
And then I escaped,
and I ran into the jungle...

55:01.595 --> 55:04.295
...then those vultures came
and tried to kill me.

55:04.365 --> 55:06.995
You wouldn't have been scared. I was.

55:07.065 --> 55:09.435
- I have to tell you something.
- What?

55:10.005 --> 55:11.475
Listen.

55:12.975 --> 55:14.565
- Get 'em, Dad!
- Run!

55:15.205 --> 55:16.835
Run!

55:17.515 --> 55:20.005
Dad, you should be chasing them!

55:20.085 --> 55:22.485
- Like you used to!
- Those were just stories!

55:22.555 --> 55:24.885
But now's your chance
to show me for real!

55:28.655 --> 55:30.415
This way!

55:33.825 --> 55:38.395
- Dad? What's goin' on?
- Just get up into that tree!

55:44.905 --> 55:47.065
- I think we lost them.
- What's the deal?

55:47.145 --> 55:49.165
They're just a bunch of wimpy donkeys!

55:49.245 --> 55:50.875
You could kick their rumps!

55:50.945 --> 55:54.505
- Ryan, I can't fight them.
- You donkey-chickens! Get back here!

55:54.585 --> 55:56.675
Ryan! I can't fight them.

55:57.585 --> 55:59.355
What do you mean?

56:01.425 --> 56:03.515
I was young...

56:03.595 --> 56:05.725
...still just a cub.

56:06.665 --> 56:08.925
Ladies and gentlemen.

56:09.005 --> 56:11.165
Children of all ages.

56:11.235 --> 56:14.565
Samson!
Swallow that fear and stand tall!

56:14.645 --> 56:18.575
Witness the greatest day
in our young lion's life!

56:18.645 --> 56:22.545
The day he discovers his roar!

56:22.615 --> 56:24.315
Dad, I can't do it!

56:24.385 --> 56:25.875
Now, go!

56:25.955 --> 56:29.855
Listen as Samson
unleashes a roar so mighty,

56:29.925 --> 56:33.385
it launches a wildebeest
clear off the savannah!

56:37.895 --> 56:40.365
Samson! Dig deep!

56:52.615 --> 56:54.105
I should have known.

56:54.185 --> 56:58.245
If you'd been born in the wild,
you'd know how to roar.

56:58.585 --> 56:59.645
Dad?

57:00.785 --> 57:03.385
Dad! Dad!

57:03.455 --> 57:05.395
Please!

57:08.195 --> 57:09.665
Dad.

57:09.735 --> 57:12.795
When they shipped me to the zoo,
I never wanted anyone to know

57:12.865 --> 57:17.105
where I came from.
Especially those closest to me.

57:17.175 --> 57:19.265
I should have told you sooner.

57:19.345 --> 57:22.775
But... all those stories you tell?

57:22.845 --> 57:25.745
I'm so sorry, Ryan.

57:25.815 --> 57:28.845
Everything you told me was a lie?

57:30.985 --> 57:33.385
- Dad!
- Hang on, son.

57:34.325 --> 57:36.295
Help!

57:36.395 --> 57:38.325
Ryan!

57:39.965 --> 57:42.095
Ryan! Run!

57:44.475 --> 57:46.495
Not so fast, Tigger.

57:48.175 --> 57:49.905
Dad!

57:51.775 --> 57:53.745
Ryan!

57:53.815 --> 57:55.245
Dad!

57:57.685 --> 58:00.585
- Help!
- Ryan.

58:00.655 --> 58:02.645
Help! Dad!

58:02.725 --> 58:05.785
- Ryan.
- Dad! Help me!

58:15.305 --> 58:16.735
What?

58:19.045 --> 58:21.035
Wait! What? What? Wait!

58:21.105 --> 58:23.375
Wait, wait, wait, wait! Hey! Hey! Hey!

58:26.785 --> 58:27.905
Get off me!

58:28.655 --> 58:30.045
What is goin' on here?

58:30.115 --> 58:34.145
- Stinky does not speak.
- It rolls like a little ball.

58:34.225 --> 58:36.025
Wait. You guys think I'm a...?

58:36.095 --> 58:39.115
<i>- Achtung, Stinky!
- Less talk, more roll.</i>

58:39.195 --> 58:41.165
<i>- Ja.
- Roll! Roll!</i>

58:41.235 --> 58:43.325
What the...? Hey!

58:43.395 --> 58:46.065
Rolling the dung is good for tight buns!

58:46.135 --> 58:48.195
I'll give you something to roll about!

58:51.745 --> 58:54.145
It's a good thing
Bridget didn't see that!

58:54.215 --> 58:57.205
Bridget? Larry! They're gone.

58:58.285 --> 58:59.515
I gotta find them!

58:59.585 --> 59:02.175
No! I gotta find Samson first!

59:02.255 --> 59:03.725
No! First...

59:08.025 --> 59:10.085
Sam. Sam!

59:22.805 --> 59:24.405
Bridget! Larry!

59:24.475 --> 59:26.245
Oh, Ryan! You're alive!

59:26.315 --> 59:28.305
Good to see you guys.

59:28.385 --> 59:30.855
- Where's my hug?
- Larry.

59:30.915 --> 59:33.685
- There it is.
- It's good to see you too.

59:35.455 --> 59:37.115
What are you guys doing here?

59:37.195 --> 59:39.455
We came here
with your father to find you.

59:39.525 --> 59:43.015
And he's probably out there
right now lookin' for us.

59:44.195 --> 59:45.995
I wish he were.

59:46.065 --> 59:48.835
But some of these wildebeests
pushed him off a cliff.

59:48.905 --> 59:50.465
- What?
- What?

59:50.535 --> 59:53.945
I don't think he made it.
I don't see how he could.

59:54.005 --> 59:55.905
Oh, Ryan.

59:55.975 --> 59:58.245
I'm sorry I got you into this.

59:58.315 --> 01:00:02.045
Kazar, I think you'll be very pleased
with what I brought you.

01:00:02.115 --> 01:00:04.585
What's this? Where's the other lion?

01:00:04.655 --> 01:00:08.355
Right. Well, I was gonna tell you,
there was this cliff and...

01:00:09.825 --> 01:00:12.695
Why are you looking at me like that?

01:00:12.765 --> 01:00:16.495
That's twice you've been
out of step today, Blag!

01:00:16.565 --> 01:00:17.825
You klutz.

01:00:17.905 --> 01:00:20.565
You know we can't ascend
to the top of the food chain

01:00:20.635 --> 01:00:23.695
until we eat a lion!

01:00:25.345 --> 01:00:28.335
Well, at least there'll
be enough for my ascension.

01:00:28.415 --> 01:00:29.935
What about the rest of us?

01:00:30.015 --> 01:00:32.845
Step-kick, pivot-kick!

01:00:38.325 --> 01:00:40.485
Ouch! I twisted a hoof!

01:00:40.555 --> 01:00:43.725
You work and you work.
Then they break your heart.

01:00:43.795 --> 01:00:48.135
- There goes my career!
- Prepare the sacrifices!

01:00:51.375 --> 01:00:53.635
Why did I let him go off by himself?

01:00:53.705 --> 01:00:57.805
He couldn't catch a cold,
much less his own lunch.

01:00:59.415 --> 01:01:01.005
Bet I could catch you.

01:01:01.085 --> 01:01:02.415
Please.

01:01:02.485 --> 01:01:05.615
My natural predator
is fuel inject... What?

01:01:05.685 --> 01:01:08.955
I knew you weren't really gone.
I knew it!

01:01:09.025 --> 01:01:12.355
Come on, I knew it!
We're still buddies, right?

01:01:13.695 --> 01:01:15.285
I lost Ryan.

01:01:15.365 --> 01:01:18.665
There were too many. They just took him.

01:01:18.735 --> 01:01:21.395
Who? Who took him?

01:01:21.475 --> 01:01:25.035
- Wildebeests.
- The freaks with the hooves!

01:01:25.105 --> 01:01:26.975
They got Larry and Bridget too.

01:01:27.045 --> 01:01:30.305
Couldn't fight, couldn't...

01:01:30.375 --> 01:01:31.975
Come on, Sam. You're a lion.

01:01:32.045 --> 01:01:34.175
You come from a long line of kings.

01:01:34.255 --> 01:01:36.515
Yeah, maybe you're not from the wild.

01:01:36.585 --> 01:01:38.575
But fighting's in your blood!

01:01:38.655 --> 01:01:42.095
No. I'll never be a real lion.

01:01:42.155 --> 01:01:45.065
Wrong! You are a real lion.

01:01:45.125 --> 01:01:47.025
Doesn't matter where you're from:

01:01:47.095 --> 01:01:49.935
Zoo, jungle, goldfish bowl.

01:01:50.005 --> 01:01:51.935
It's what's in here.

01:01:52.005 --> 01:01:54.305
That determines who you are!

01:01:54.375 --> 01:01:56.865
At least, that's what you
always told your son.

01:01:56.945 --> 01:01:59.435
Now he's out there, Sammy,

01:01:59.515 --> 01:02:02.535
and he needs you.

01:02:02.615 --> 01:02:05.135
Who else is gonna
teach him how to roar?

01:02:09.555 --> 01:02:10.955
That's it, Sammy.

01:02:16.325 --> 01:02:17.595
That's it.

01:02:23.165 --> 01:02:26.905
Let's go find my son...
and my friends.

01:02:26.975 --> 01:02:29.565
Yeah! Nothing's gonna stop us!

01:02:29.645 --> 01:02:33.045
Except that we have no idea
where we're going!

01:02:34.145 --> 01:02:35.805
Follow your instincts.

01:02:35.885 --> 01:02:37.545
Follow your instincts.

01:02:37.615 --> 01:02:41.885
- What is that?
- My... instincts?

01:02:45.825 --> 01:02:48.455
- Benny?
- You're almost there.

01:02:49.865 --> 01:02:51.125
That settles it, then.

01:02:51.195 --> 01:02:54.865
My mother definitely drank pool water
when she was pregnant with me.

01:02:54.935 --> 01:02:56.465
Benny, look.

01:02:56.535 --> 01:02:58.905
The freaks with hooves!

01:02:58.975 --> 01:03:00.305
Ryan's in there.

01:03:01.545 --> 01:03:03.735
You can't just barge in. That's suicide!

01:03:03.815 --> 01:03:07.345
- Benny, get out of my way!
- Don't listen to the rat.

01:03:07.415 --> 01:03:10.405
- Hey, who are you calling a rat?
- You, of course.

01:03:10.485 --> 01:03:13.945
- You'll give away our position.
- I'll have you written up for that!

01:03:14.025 --> 01:03:17.225
Fool! You blew our cover!
Men! Scatter!

01:03:18.265 --> 01:03:20.425
Not so fast!

01:03:20.495 --> 01:03:23.935
Look who I got, Sammy.
It's your lion instincts.

01:03:24.005 --> 01:03:25.365
Who are you guys?

01:03:25.435 --> 01:03:28.135
- Our names aren't important.
- I'm Cloak. He's Camo.

01:03:28.205 --> 01:03:31.375
- We're covert agents.
- Why have you been leading me around?

01:03:31.445 --> 01:03:33.805
- That's classified.
- Top-secret.

01:03:33.875 --> 01:03:35.975
- The wildebeests have gone mad.
- Cloak.

01:03:36.045 --> 01:03:39.485
It's not like I told them our plan
is to use them to defeat Kazar's...

01:03:39.555 --> 01:03:42.385
Listen, just tell me,
did they take my son in there?

01:03:42.455 --> 01:03:44.255
- That's need-to-know.
- They did.

01:03:44.325 --> 01:03:47.555
- They think the koala's a god.
- You're the worst covert agent!

01:03:47.625 --> 01:03:50.065
Oh, yeah?
Then why can I do this? Men!

01:03:50.135 --> 01:03:52.895
Hey! No! Stop! Sammy!

01:03:52.965 --> 01:03:57.265
- Idiot! That maneuver's confidential.
- It's secret. This one's confidential.

01:03:57.335 --> 01:03:59.275
- Cloak!
- And this one's restricted.

01:03:59.345 --> 01:04:03.145
Super-secret.
Top-secret. This is ultra-secret!

01:04:03.215 --> 01:04:04.705
Enough! No more!

01:04:04.775 --> 01:04:08.405
Show 'em the super-top-secret
"no more?" Gotcha!

01:04:08.485 --> 01:04:09.505
No!

01:04:11.355 --> 01:04:12.685
I got an idea.

01:04:16.555 --> 01:04:19.585
Who is this Great Him, anyway?
I'll take him on.

01:04:19.665 --> 01:04:22.065
I'm the Great Her!
I'll show Him a thing or two.

01:04:22.135 --> 01:04:24.565
I'm from New York City, for Pete's sake.

01:04:25.635 --> 01:04:27.155
Oh, my.

01:04:41.285 --> 01:04:43.655
You have got to be kidding me.

01:04:52.795 --> 01:04:55.525
Nigel, I don't know
what you're trying to pull,

01:04:55.605 --> 01:04:57.655
- but I will kick your...
- Silence!

01:04:58.605 --> 01:05:00.665
Why, you little...

01:05:00.735 --> 01:05:02.435
Silence, again!

01:05:02.505 --> 01:05:05.905
You do not speak to me!

01:05:05.975 --> 01:05:07.415
Nigel, what's the deal?

01:05:07.485 --> 01:05:10.415
Great Him, shall we prepare the feast?

01:05:10.485 --> 01:05:14.015
Yes, we shall! What's on the menu?

01:05:14.085 --> 01:05:15.485
Them.

01:05:16.625 --> 01:05:18.145
Oh, no.

01:05:18.225 --> 01:05:20.885
Eat friends and be god,
don't eat friends...

01:05:20.965 --> 01:05:23.295
God, friends, god, friends. God, I...

01:05:23.365 --> 01:05:24.955
Well, that was subtle.

01:05:25.035 --> 01:05:26.195
Prepare the meat fire!

01:05:29.875 --> 01:05:31.425
Wait!

01:05:33.375 --> 01:05:36.635
We cannot cook them without...

01:05:38.075 --> 01:05:39.175
...onion!

01:05:39.245 --> 01:05:42.705
Onions. Onions. Onions.

01:05:43.915 --> 01:05:45.815
Well, that was fast.

01:05:45.885 --> 01:05:48.015
Let the ritual begin.

01:05:52.125 --> 01:05:53.455
Move it!

01:05:53.525 --> 01:05:55.825
I am so mad at you!

01:05:56.965 --> 01:06:01.195
Wait! We also need... hats!

01:06:02.675 --> 01:06:06.305
Do we not have the party hats of death?

01:06:06.375 --> 01:06:07.935
I've got mine!

01:06:08.015 --> 01:06:11.675
And before the feast, we must all...

01:06:12.085 --> 01:06:13.675
What the...?

01:06:14.555 --> 01:06:15.785
...levitate...

01:06:15.855 --> 01:06:17.715
...and spin uncontrollably!

01:06:17.785 --> 01:06:20.385
And feel a bit sick.

01:06:21.295 --> 01:06:22.625
How do I stop this thing?

01:06:22.695 --> 01:06:24.425
- Guys.
- Benny?

01:06:24.495 --> 01:06:26.525
- Look, a squirrel!
- Larry!

01:06:27.435 --> 01:06:29.365
We've got a plan. Follow me.

01:06:29.435 --> 01:06:32.025
- We?
- I can fly!

01:06:32.105 --> 01:06:35.565
Oh, Great Him,
we are humbled by your power.

01:06:35.645 --> 01:06:39.505
Be humbled.
Only the Great Him can do this!

01:06:41.985 --> 01:06:44.105
- Volcanic gas!
- Our cover's blown!

01:06:44.185 --> 01:06:46.675
Major malfunction! Abandon ship!

01:06:55.265 --> 01:06:58.665
- Oh, boy.
- Well, about time you got here.

01:06:58.735 --> 01:07:01.395
Great Him, it's another miracle!

01:07:01.465 --> 01:07:04.665
You've delivered us a real lion!

01:07:04.735 --> 01:07:06.865
Blag, your luck has turned.

01:07:06.945 --> 01:07:11.275
Thanks to the Great Him,
we shall all ascend tonight.

01:07:11.345 --> 01:07:14.335
Nigel, we've got
to create a distraction.

01:07:15.255 --> 01:07:16.545
Hang on a sec!

01:07:16.615 --> 01:07:19.285
I've got miracles comin' out my ears!

01:07:19.355 --> 01:07:22.515
Ready? Stand back...

01:07:22.595 --> 01:07:26.185
...as the Great Me attacks the lion

01:07:26.265 --> 01:07:29.795
over 73 times my size!

01:07:33.535 --> 01:07:36.705
Dad? My dad's alive!
Guys, my dad made it!

01:07:36.775 --> 01:07:38.575
- Ryan, no!
- Hurry, I got to see him!

01:07:42.515 --> 01:07:43.985
Whack, whack, whack!

01:07:44.045 --> 01:07:45.445
- Dad!
- What? Ryan!

01:07:47.055 --> 01:07:49.815
- I planned this.
- Ryan, no!

01:07:54.665 --> 01:07:57.895
At long last,
the cosmic balance has shifted.

01:07:57.965 --> 01:08:00.765
- Stay close.
- Prey has become predator!

01:08:00.835 --> 01:08:02.735
And predator has become prey!

01:08:02.805 --> 01:08:05.435
And the hoof finally trumps the claw!

01:08:05.505 --> 01:08:08.335
Come on, Dad!
Let's show these turkey-jerkies

01:08:08.405 --> 01:08:10.535
who's at the top of the food chain!

01:08:12.345 --> 01:08:14.815
Let's eat the brat first.

01:08:15.145 --> 01:08:18.145
Over my dead body!

01:08:31.965 --> 01:08:33.595
Yeah.

01:08:35.135 --> 01:08:36.725
Dad!

01:08:40.205 --> 01:08:42.835
He's gonna kill Samson
if we don't do something!

01:08:42.915 --> 01:08:45.604
Why don't we use the secret play?

01:08:45.685 --> 01:08:49.444
I know. Shut up, Larry. That's stupid.

01:08:49.515 --> 01:08:51.854
No! It's brilliant!

01:08:51.925 --> 01:08:54.685
They laughed at me
when I spoke of the Omen.

01:08:54.755 --> 01:08:58.385
But look who's laughing now!

01:09:03.935 --> 01:09:06.805
Little to the left. Yeah.
No! Little to the right!

01:09:06.875 --> 01:09:09.635
Next floor: bottom of the food chain!

01:09:09.875 --> 01:09:11.274
Ding!

01:09:12.145 --> 01:09:13.335
Fire!

01:09:20.615 --> 01:09:23.285
We gotta find something bigger!

01:09:23.354 --> 01:09:25.825
I know where we can
find something bigger.

01:09:29.564 --> 01:09:31.854
- Ready, Ryan?
- Dig deep!

01:09:31.935 --> 01:09:33.555
You should have stayed at home.

01:09:33.635 --> 01:09:36.895
Now our shrine will become your tomb.

01:09:36.975 --> 01:09:38.335
Fire!

01:09:45.715 --> 01:09:47.575
Ryan!

01:09:48.955 --> 01:09:49.935
Ryan!

01:09:51.915 --> 01:09:54.015
I don't typically eat dessert

01:09:54.085 --> 01:09:56.215
before the main course!

01:09:56.725 --> 01:09:59.315
Get away from my son!

01:10:08.775 --> 01:10:09.935
Ryan.

01:10:16.545 --> 01:10:19.745
Ryan, are you still with me?

01:10:19.815 --> 01:10:24.015
It's OK, Dad. I just want you to know

01:10:24.085 --> 01:10:28.655
I'm sorry you didn't have a father
like the one I have.

01:10:28.725 --> 01:10:30.385
Ryan.

01:10:33.065 --> 01:10:34.895
How touching.

01:10:34.965 --> 01:10:37.795
But then, last words usually are.

01:10:39.975 --> 01:10:41.195
Finish them.

01:10:50.085 --> 01:10:51.635
What are you doing?

01:10:51.715 --> 01:10:55.515
I command you to attack them,
like true predators!

01:10:55.585 --> 01:10:58.925
We're tired of pretending
to be something we're not.

01:10:58.995 --> 01:11:03.125
But most of all, we're tired of you.

01:11:06.465 --> 01:11:09.065
Blag. Fine.

01:11:09.135 --> 01:11:11.035
I'll kill them myself!

01:11:16.575 --> 01:11:20.065
Dad, remember what you
always told me in your stories:

01:11:20.145 --> 01:11:21.545
Dig deep.

01:11:40.205 --> 01:11:43.065
Oh, yeah, baby!

01:12:05.125 --> 01:12:06.465
Let's go.

01:12:06.535 --> 01:12:08.625
Yeah.

01:12:08.695 --> 01:12:11.265
- Come on, let's get out of here!
- Get out of here!

01:12:11.335 --> 01:12:15.035
And for the record,
I've always hated your choreography.

01:12:15.105 --> 01:12:17.945
It's so... '80s.

01:12:19.945 --> 01:12:21.345
That's right! Run!

01:12:21.415 --> 01:12:23.935
Run like the cowardly prey that you are!

01:12:24.015 --> 01:12:26.005
I will hunt you down!

01:12:28.425 --> 01:12:30.255
Everyone! To the boat!

01:12:30.325 --> 01:12:32.085
Top of the food chain, Ma!

01:12:32.155 --> 01:12:35.455
Top of the food chain...

01:12:35.525 --> 01:12:39.465
<i>I'm so cuddly! I like you!
I'm so cuddly! I like you!</i>

01:12:39.535 --> 01:12:41.895
<i>I'm so cuddly! I like you!
I'm so cuddly!</i>

01:12:50.515 --> 01:12:52.815
Hurry! We're never gonna make it!

01:12:52.885 --> 01:12:55.615
Push, you crazy, hairy monsters! Push!

01:12:56.715 --> 01:13:00.015
- Larry, throw it in reverse!
- Reverse throwing!

01:13:11.505 --> 01:13:15.025
At least I saw the wild
before it disappeared.

01:13:15.105 --> 01:13:17.595
I can still see it. It's right...

01:13:17.675 --> 01:13:20.605
Here. I found my roar.

01:13:21.145 --> 01:13:23.665
We both did, son.

01:13:24.385 --> 01:13:28.755
You know, Dad, this'll be our first
story of Samson and Ryan the Wild.

01:13:28.815 --> 01:13:31.085
I don't think anybody's
gonna believe it.

01:13:34.025 --> 01:13:35.995
Incoming!

01:13:41.195 --> 01:13:43.325
<i>I'm so cuddly!</i>

01:13:43.405 --> 01:13:46.535
<i>Cuddly! I'm so cuddly!</i>

01:13:46.605 --> 01:13:49.595
I know you're cuddly. But can you float?

01:13:52.545 --> 01:13:54.605
<i>- I'm having a
- Really nice day</i>

01:13:54.685 --> 01:13:56.545
<i>Really nice day
Really nice day</i>

01:13:56.615 --> 01:13:58.555
Step-kick left!

01:13:58.615 --> 01:14:00.315
<i>Really nice day</i>

01:14:00.385 --> 01:14:01.375
Step-kick right!

01:14:02.685 --> 01:14:05.085
- Splendid.
- No! Smashing. Hey!

01:14:05.155 --> 01:14:07.555
- Stupendous!
- Are you guys sure about this?

01:14:07.625 --> 01:14:09.825
Operation Snake-Over is now complete.

01:14:09.895 --> 01:14:12.765
Hey, look, everyone! I'm a secret agent!

01:14:14.535 --> 01:14:17.565
Bridget, I get it. You're more
than a tall, lanky goddess.

01:14:17.635 --> 01:14:19.695
You're a strong, independent female.

01:14:19.775 --> 01:14:22.295
You don't need to be defined
by your relationship

01:14:22.375 --> 01:14:24.675
- and I, I respect that.
- It's about time.

01:14:27.745 --> 01:14:29.215
What was that?

01:14:29.285 --> 01:14:33.185
Just your daily dose
of vitamin Bridget, baby.

01:14:33.255 --> 01:14:34.815
Oh, yeah yeah!

01:14:34.895 --> 01:14:36.555
<i>Really nice day
Really nice day</i>

01:14:36.625 --> 01:14:37.615
Look out!

01:14:40.635 --> 01:14:42.995
Step-kick, pivot-kick,
walk, walk, walk.

01:14:43.065 --> 01:14:46.435
Yes! Did y'all see that? Check this!

01:14:46.505 --> 01:14:49.735
Go, Blag! Go, Blag! Go, Blag!

01:14:49.805 --> 01:14:51.635
Hey, Blag.

01:14:51.705 --> 01:14:55.205
- No parkin' on the dance floor.
- Parkin'?

01:14:55.275 --> 01:14:56.545
Dad?

01:14:56.615 --> 01:14:59.105
Make some room there, big guy!

01:15:00.755 --> 01:15:03.245
<i>Really nice day
Really, really nice day</i>

01:15:03.325 --> 01:15:05.485
Yeah!

01:15:06.255 --> 01:15:09.625
Pretty crazy, right? Pretty wild!

01:15:12.435 --> 01:15:14.695
Well, technically, it...

01:15:14.765 --> 01:15:17.135
It's awesome.

01:15:17.205 --> 01:15:19.505
Yes, right.

01:15:19.575 --> 01:15:22.475
- I was just gonna say that.
- Come on! Everyone!

01:15:26.415 --> 01:15:28.475
This is gonna be a long ride home.

01:15:28.545 --> 01:15:30.105
<i>I'm havin' a</i>

01:15:30.185 --> 01:15:34.175
<i>Really nice day
Really nice day, really nice day</i>

01:15:34.255 --> 01:15:37.155
<i>- I'm having a
- I'm so cuddly, I like you</i>

01:15:37.225 --> 01:15:38.695
<i>G'day</i>

01:15:41.425 --> 01:15:44.485
What are you doing this for?
What, do you think it's funny?

01:15:44.565 --> 01:15:46.155
Just get out.

01:15:46.235 --> 01:15:48.165
Sorry about that, everybody. Sorry.

01:15:48.235 --> 01:15:49.665
Hello.

01:15:50.705 --> 01:15:52.365
Do carry on.

01:16:25.645 --> 01:16:27.235
Come on!

01:21:19.925 --> 01:21:22.865
All right,
